repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

commit.message: Fix a temp leak in the type init code.
Fix temp leaks in fused types initialisation code.
It looks like we have a C++ compatible way to store C array temps on the stack now and no longer need to leak array temp variables.
Correctly release the buffer index temps allocated for index calculations.
Make tests fails hard if a temp variable is not released at the end of a generated function.
Fix temp leak in switch statement code.
Make end-to-end tests fail on refnanny output.
Fix result temp leak in PyTypeTestNode.
Fix result temp leak in external type/function import code and enable the refnanny check for them.

Revert "It looks like we have a C++ compatible way to store C array temps on the stack now and no longer need to leak array temp variables."

This reverts commit 62ec37bb879a44da8264b9cd77a4095d8e8a9371.
Fix temp leak when try-return-finally is used in generators.
Make it explicit when an allocated temp is not meant to be reused.

Make error message on temp failures more greppable.
Also remove the sort key since the first tuple item is unique.
Make temp validation work for literal lists again (which use stack allocated C arrays) and improve the temp debug output for zombie temps.
Fix temp leak when assigning to the real/imag attributes of complex numbers.
Fix temp leak when assigning to a memoryview slice.
Clean up "num_threads" result temp in parallel section, not only in prange loop.
Fix temp leak in Pythran buffer setitem code.

Simplify NumPyMethodCallNode since it does not need the Python function anymore.
Previously, it generated code that needlessly looked up the Python function without actually using it.
Fix temp leak when deleting C++ objects.
Add a test that actually reusing temps when deleting C++ objects works correctly.

milestone.description:
Goals:
– New version scheme: 3.x instead of 0.x.
– Change default `language_level` from `2` to `3`.
– Change default for `binding` directive from `False` to `True`.
– Fix some Python compatibility issues (if possible, allowing for breaking changes).
